The paper proposes a method based on deep learning for cardiac segmentation on MRI images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method involves the use of a novel variant of U-net, which is a popular deep learning architecture for image segmentation, indicating the relevance of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a large database for training and testing, which suggests the relevance of multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper emphasizes the generalization ability of the proposed method to unseen cases, indicating the relevance of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
